# Mobile Responsiveness Rules

## Mobile-First Approach
All components and pages must be designed mobile-first, then enhanced for larger screens.

### Breakpoint Strategy
Use Tailwind CSS breakpoints consistently:
- `sm:` - 640px+ (small tablets)
- `md:` - 768px+ (tablets)
- `lg:` - 1024px+ (laptops)
- `xl:` - 1280px+ (desktops)

### Layout Patterns
```html
<!-- ✅ Mobile-first grid -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">

<!-- ✅ Responsive spacing -->
<div class="p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8">

<!-- ✅ Responsive text -->
<h1 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl lg:text-3xl">
```

### Navigation Requirements
- Mobile menu must be collapsible using `data-mobile-menu-toggle`
- Desktop navigation should hide on mobile (`hidden md:flex`)
- Mobile menu should slide in/out smoothly
- Touch-friendly button sizes (minimum 44px)

### Form Responsiveness
```html
<!-- ✅ Responsive form layout -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <input class="w-full px-3 py-2 text-sm sm:text-base">
```

### Image and Media
- Use responsive images with `max-w-full h-auto`
- Videos should be responsive with aspect ratio containers
- Icons should scale appropriately on mobile

### Typography Scaling
```html
<!-- ✅ Responsive typography -->
<h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl">
<p class="text-sm sm:text-base lg:text-lg">
```

### Spacing Guidelines
- Use consistent spacing scale: `space-y-4 sm:space-y-6 lg:space-y-8`
- Padding should increase on larger screens: `p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8`
- Margins should be responsive: `m-4 sm:m-6 lg:m-8`

### Touch Targets
- Minimum 44px touch targets for interactive elements
- Adequate spacing between clickable elements
- Use `touch-manipulation` CSS for better touch response

